    "title": "Object Pronouns: le, la, les",
    "explanation": "Un homme arrive ici. Avril le regarde bien. — who does Avril look at? Le replaces l'homme. The pronoun goes BEFORE the verb.\n\nNotice the pattern: [subject] + le/la + [verb]. Avril le regarde. She looks at HIM.\n\nRe-read and find every le/la that comes before a verb. What noun does each one replace?"
